title: Grateful Dead Live at Jai-Alai Fronton on 1974-06-23
description:
Set 1

Ramble On Rose, Black Throated Wind, Mississippi Half Step, Beat It On Down The Line, Row Jimmy, Jack Straw, Let It Rock, Cumberland Blues, El Paso, To Lay Me Down, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow-> China Doll

Set 2

Phil & Ned-> Ship of Fools, Big River, Black Peter, Around & Around, Dark Star-> Spanish Jam-> U.S. Blues, Uncle John's Band-> One More Saturday Night, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: Amazing sound A great update to an already killer matrix. This show has perfect levels. Thanks again Hunter!

Jesus Christ with egg in his beard This sounds better than any official release. Just click on Black Peter. Keith's keyboards have that wonderful tone you hear all over Blues for Allah. I wonder why they always played so well in Florida? Maybe it was the blow.

Wow! Great sound & great playing. Even the "bathroom break" songs are terrific on this one! The transition from "Spanish Jam" to "U.S. Blues" is like nothing else I've heard them do. WRS is at its peak here. The only flaw comes at the very end of OMSN when somebody on stage stepped on a cat.

Bravo! Bellissimo!

One of the best shows of an incredable month, combined with amazing SQ.

Let it Rock! It is songs like these that make kids want to grow up to become rock ‘n’ roll stars! And makes me want to grab to strat, plug-in, and become the group’s 3rd guitarist and jam along with. Great show, great rhythm and blues songs, and all pure rock ‘n’ roll!
Tuning->Jam->Ship of Fools Listen at daybreak...Pure Delight
Amazing show; great mix Top notch choice.
